<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/Forum9/HTML/001311.html">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ashock</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hello.<P>First, I just want to say to the Larian people who read this forum that I am enjoying this game a lot. I'm a long time Diablo, Diablo2 and BIS games player, and I have to say that this is the first game in a while that has been very enjoyable to me, and that  includes the fact that I have played DS, NWN and IWD2 recently. Even if the ending turns out to be a letdown for me (which seems to be the consensus here), I still consider this game money well spent. DD seems to incorporate many of the better features of D, D2 and BG2 and even if it's a ripoff (and I'm not saying it is), I don't care.<P>Ok, now to the questions.<P><BR>1) Is there any 1-handed swords in the game with a higher base damage than a bastard sword? I was all pumped up when I saw my first deathsword, since it looked like a 1-hander to me, and I even reloaded a bunch of times to get one with frost (which btw, is way too powerful). Suffice it to say that by the time I got to 45 Dex and was able to use it, I was slightly disappointed ;-)<P>2) Stormfist Castle - if I enter it, it does not mean that I am taking the road to the finale, does it? I have read some posts that stated that it's just another area of the game and nothing more, but for some reason I also seem to recall from somewhere that Stormfist leads to a point of no return, so to speak. If I am mistaken about that, when *is* that point?<P><BR>TIA<P>-A</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ariana</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> Stormfist Castle loses you your teleporter stones until you do something to get them back so it is convenient to finish most of what is available before going in. But you do come out again and can move around the map - just without the stones for a while.<P>I haven't gotten every type of sword, not having come all that close to the end, but I haven't seen any 1H swords with really good base damage. OTOH the smith in the Market just happened to have a bastard sword with +4 freeze +3 stun my first visit. I almost dropped the mouse, but recovered fast enough to buy the sword. I have sold quite a few swords with much higher base damage since then and kept this one.<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">maeloran</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't know if there are better one-handers. Why not go with an axe, btw? They do more base damage. Then again, more armor (shield in this case) comes at a cost. Or medium damage and a shield, or high damage without a shield. It all levels out I guess..<P>For entering the Castle: no, it doesn't mean you can't get back. I'm not going to spoil anything, but it's just part of the main story. In fact, no where near then end! I entered stormfist at lvl 18 or so, am now lvl 25 and I guess the castle is about a quarter or a third in the game.<P>Have fun!</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">maeloran</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by ariana:<BR><I> Stormfist Castle loses you your teleporter stones</I><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I still don't have them back, and I'm just now trudging through verdistis..... So I didn't do the right thing here? And can you spoil it and tell me when the H**L I'm getting my stones back?? I miss my stones!!<P></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</IFRAME>
